``` verilator tb_zcounter.sv zcounter.sv  --binary --trace```


What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
5.034 compiled with clang-18 

What OS and distribution are you using?
ubuntu20.04

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
Sure , but we need clarify reason first. 



After executing the simple bench below, the waveform data obtained shows inconsistencies between the results calculated by Verilator and VCS. According to common understanding, both Verilator and VCS comply with the IEEE Verilog standard. However, in actual simulations, they produce different waveform outputs, which is quite puzzling. What is the reason for this discrepancy? Or, how can such differences be avoided?

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/06ba270d-ab92-4669-9ecc-6546b3770298)

```verilog
module zcounter(
input clk,
input rstn,
input [7:0] d
);

reg [7:0]cnt;
initial begin
// #1 $display("reseted");
end

always @(posedge clk or rstn)
begin
    if(!rstn)
        cnt <= 0;
    else
        cnt <= cnt + 1;
end

logic [7:0] left_idx_cnt;
logic [7:0] left_idx_cnt_d;


always @(posedge clk or rstn) begin
    if(!rstn)
        left_idx_cnt_d <= 'h40;
    else
        left_idx_cnt_d<= left_idx_cnt;
end
logic [7:0] idx_mask_head;
logic [7:0] idx_mask_cnt;

wire [7:0] start_to_boundary_cnt= cnt-idx_mask_head;

always @* begin
    if(cnt<=6) begin
        idx_mask_head =8;
        left_idx_cnt=10;
        idx_mask_cnt=6;
    end else begin
        idx_mask_head = 0;
        left_idx_cnt = left_idx_cnt_d - idx_mask_cnt;
        idx_mask_cnt =start_to_boundary_cnt-1;
    end
end

endmodule
```

```verilog
`timescale 1ps/1ps

module tb_zcounter;

  // Inputs to DUT
  reg clk;
  reg rstn;
  reg [7:0] d;

  // Instantiate the Device Under Test (DUT)
  zcounter dut (
      .clk(clk),
      .rstn(rstn),
      .d(d)
  );

  // Clock generation (e.g., 100MHz = 10ns = 10000ps period -> 5000ps half-period)
  // Using 10ps half-period from the example image for consistency
  initial begin
    clk = 1;
    forever #10 clk = ~clk; // 20ps clock period
  end

  // Stimulus generation
  initial begin
    // Initialize signals
    rstn = 0; // Assert reset
    d = 0;

    // Deassert reset after some time
    #30 rstn = 1;

    // Apply input value after reset is deasserted
    #60 d = 3; // Apply d=3 at time 30ps + 60ps = 90ps


  end

  // Simulation control
  initial begin
    #1000; // Run simulation for 1000ps
    $finish;
  end

  // Waveform dumping
  initial begin
    $dumpfile("zcounter_wave.vcd");
    $dumpvars(0, tb_zcounter); // Dump all signals in this module and below
  end

endmodule
```
